                },
                {
                    "title": "<span style=\"font-size:26px\">&nbsp;</span>",
                    "content": "<div class=\"methodology\">\n<h1 class=\"methodology-subtitle\">About the data</h1>\n<div class=\"methodology-definitions\">\n<h2>Definitions</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"concept\">The proportion of youth (aged 15\u201424) in Brazil who are not in employment, education or training (also known as \"the youth NEET rate\")</span>: <span class=\"definition\">This indicator refers to young people in that age cohort who are not employed and who are outside the educational system, that is, not enrolled in formal/regular education or in training to gain entry to tertiary education or technical education or to obtain professional qualifications.</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"methodology-coverage\">\n<h2>Coverage</h2>\n<p>Youth population aged 15\u201424.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"methodology-availability\">\n<h2>Availability</h2>\n<p>Data are available from national and subnational indicators.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n",
